# Auto commit and push

After completing any code update in this project:

1. Commit all relevant changes with a concise message (focus on why, not what).
2. Push to `origin` on the current branch without waiting for the user to ask.
3. Briefly confirm commit hash and that push succeeded in the final reply.

Do not commit files with secrets (`.env`, credentials). Do not force-push to main.

If there are no changes to commit, skip commit/push and say so.
